<p><cs><col><b>Cholic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a complex
organic acid found as a natural constituent of taurocholic and
glycocholic acids in the bile, and extracted as a resinous substance,
convertible under the influence of ether into white
crystals.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

